  "keywords": [],
  "notes": [
    "Don’t put sauce on the bread, it’ll make it wet — put it between other layers.",
    "You can cook the sauce up to several days in advance, and store it in the fridge."
  ],
  "overnight": false,
  "slug": "klatz-burger",
  "source": "",
  "steps": [
    {
      "name": "",
      "steps": [
        {
          "text": "**Prepare your preferred sauce:** [first world salsa verde](/recipes/salsa-verde-de/), [salsa roja tatemada](/recipes/charred-red-sauce/), or another of your choice.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Heat two skillets on medium heat.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Prepare the vegetables.<br>\n**Bell pepper:** remove the stem and seeds, cut the top and the bottom, cut the middle part into 3-4 squares (one bell pepper is enough for 5-6 burgers).<br>\n**Tomato:** slice thinly.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "On the first skillet, increase the heat to medium-high, add a bit of olive oil, and **cook the bell peppers**, until softened a bit, and slightly blistered on both sides.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "On the second skillet, add a bit of olive oil, and **fry the eggs**: crack each egg into the hot oil, sprinkle with salt, and cover the skillet. Fry covered until all the whites are fully set.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "While the eggs and bell peppers are cooking, **form the burger patties**: mix the ground meat just enough to combine, divide into 100 g portions, roll into balls, and gently press into round patties. (Avoid mixing and pressing too much, as it'll make the patties harder when they are cooked.)",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "On the skillet you used for the bell pepper, **fry the patties**: lower the heat to medium, add more oil if needed, place patties on the skillet, gently press down with a spatula and hold for about 10 seconds, and cook for about 5 minutes; turn and cook for 2 minutes, then put two slices of cheese on top of each patty, cover the skillet, and cook for about 5 minutes more until the internal temperature of the meat is 60C (for medium-well).",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "While the patties are cooking, on the other skillet, **toast the buns**: melt a tablespoon of butter, and toast the cut sides until golden brown.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Finally, **assemble the burgers**: lower bun, bell peppers, pickled cucumbers and/or jalapeños, patty, tomatoes, sauce, fried egg, upper bun.",
          "pause": false
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
